30/12/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Coast Guard authorities announced on Tuesday (December 29th) that Somali pirates have seized a Greek-owned cargo ship sailing under the Panamanian flag. 
The vessel, the Navios Apollon, was attacked by a group of about ten pirates in two speedboats approximately 240 nautical miles northwest of the Seychelles. 
The ship, with 19 people aboard, was transporting fertilizer from the US state of Florida to India. 
(DPA, Reuters, Ethnos, Eleftherotypia, ANA-MPA - 29/12/09)
